## 5. PRE-RECORDING RESEARCH

### Required Before Recording Each Video
- [ ] Visit their website — have it open and loaded
- [ ] Know the founder's first name
- [ ] Know what the company does in one sentence
- [ ] Know who their buyer is (the person who pays them)
- [ ] Find one specific detail to reference (client name, funding round, recent product launch, specific feature)
- [ ] Know one gap or opportunity you can frame as the hook

### Hook Formulation
The hook is the most important part. It must be:
- Specific to their company (not generic)
- An observation about an opportunity, not a problem
- Something that makes them think "this person actually looked at my site"

**Hook formula:** `[Specific observation about product/position] + [The opportunity/gap this creates]`

**Examples:**
- "AI copilot for construction supers is a sharp wedge — every GC has the problem, nobody's solved the documentation side this cleanly."
- "Most IP teams are sitting on portfolios worth millions and doing nothing with them — Patent Watch is the first tool I've seen that actually makes that actionable."
- "BPM partnering with Kipsi is a strong signal — R&D tax credit work is painful and manual at every firm."

