## 6. LOOM VIDEO FRAMEWORK

### Technical Setup
- Record ON their website (not a blank screen, not your own site)
- Face bubble visible in corner (small webcam overlay)
- CTA button set in Loom: link to Calendly (tj-signalux)
- Button placement: top right
- Button label: "[First Name] — grab time here" or "Book a call"
- Video length: 90–120 seconds maximum

### Video Title Formula
```
How [Company] can [specific outcome] with [specific buyer type]
```

**Examples:**
- `How Fresco can build a predictable demo pipeline with the right GCs`
- `How Patent Watch can get in front of enterprise IP teams consistently`
- `How Casepal can build a predictable pipeline of law firm decision makers`

### Script Structure (7 beats)

```
BEAT 1 — PERSONAL TOUCH (5–7 seconds)
"Hey [First Name], Teja here — recorded this specifically for you and [Company]."
Open on their website. Establish it's personal.

BEAT 2 — HOOK (10–15 seconds)
One sharp observation about their product, position, or timing.
NOT a compliment. An insight. Make them think "this person gets it."

BEAT 3 — THE GAP (5–10 seconds)
Name the specific problem this creates or the opportunity they're missing.
Frame it as an opportunity, not a criticism.

BEAT 4 — AUTHORITY (15–20 seconds)
"My team and I have run growth for 30+ B2B SaaS companies and helped them 
generate 1,000+ qualified demo calls — using AI-automated outbound, SEO, and ads."
Do NOT mention ad spend dollar amounts. Founders don't respond to it.
Do NOT name the specific methods in detail. Keep it vague.

BEAT 5 — SOFT OFFER (10–15 seconds)
"We built a system that gets you in front of the exact right [buyer type] 
predictably every month."
Never name the process. Outcome specific, method vague.

BEAT 6 — RISK REVERSAL (5–7 seconds)
"We guarantee 30 qualified demos in 60 days or you don't pay a cent."
State it confidently. Don't over-explain it.

BEAT 7 — CTA (10–15 seconds)
"[First Name], if you're open to [outcome] — let's talk. 
Recorded this personally, will personally reply. Button top right."
Assume the reply. Don't ask permission.
```

### What to NEVER Say in the Video
- ❌ Any specific channel: "email", "ads", "Facebook", "Google", "funnels"
- ❌ Ad spend amounts: "$10M in ad spend"
- ❌ Generic CTAs: "let me know what you think"
- ❌ Desperate language: "I'd love the opportunity", "would you be open to"
- ❌ Corporate language: "leverage synergies", "holistic approach"
- ❌ Dashes in copy (AI slop signal)

### Recording Speed Target
- 4 minutes per video including website loading and setup
- 7 videos = 28–30 minutes
- Record in one session, send immediately after

