## 9. LINKEDIN OUTREACH FRAMEWORK

### Connection Request Rules
- Send same day as cold email (Day 1)
- Connection note only — no link, no pitch, no Loom
- Under 200 characters
- End with "Wanted to connect." (period, not exclamation)
- Sound human — like you actually looked at their profile

### Connection Note Formula
```
"Hey [First Name] — [one specific observation about their company or background]. Wanted to connect."
```

**Examples:**
- "Hey Arvind — love what you're building with Fresco. The construction documentation problem is way bigger than people realize. Wanted to connect."
- "Hey Jason — JP Morgan to YC founder is a bold move. The finance workflow automation angle with Lucite is spot on. Wanted to connect."
- "Hey Claire — the Deloitte to founder path is a strong one. What you're building with Kipsi for R&D tax credit work is a real pain point. Wanted to connect."

### LinkedIn Sequence (if no email reply)
```
Day 1  → Connection request (no pitch, no link)
Day 5  → If accepted: Send Loom DM (short, under 5 lines)
Day 8  → If no reply: One-line follow up
Day 12 → Final DM (different angle)
```

### LinkedIn DM Rules (post-connection)
- Maximum 3–5 lines per message
- Each message has ONE job and ONE angle
- Never repeat offer language across messages
- Never send Loom link in connection request
- Don't wait for acceptance before sending email — email goes Day 1 regardless

