## 11. REPLY HANDLING & LEAD MAGNET

### Reply-First Flow
```
They reply (any reply, positive or question)
    ↓
Send GTM Engine output for their company
(signalux.co/gtm — run their company through it, send the output)
    ↓
They engage with the output
    ↓
Ask for 20-minute call
    ↓
They book → Discovery call
```

### GTM Engine Lead Magnet
- Live at: signalux-gtm-engine.vercel.app
- Covers 7 workstreams: Product Deep Dive, Competitive Research, ICP Definition, Positioning Strategy, Landing Page Copy, GTM Roadmap, Outbound Sequence
- Framing: "I'll build your entire GTM system for free"
- Send the OUTPUT specific to their company — not just the link

### Handling Common Replies

**"Interested, tell me more"**
→ Send GTM output first. Then ask: "Would a 20-min call make sense to walk through how this would work for [Company] specifically?"

**"Not the right time"**
→ "Totally understand — when would be a better time? Happy to check back in [timeframe]."

**"We already have someone for this"**
→ "Makes sense. Out of curiosity — are they focused on [specific outcome] or more general marketing?" (Qualify the competitor, don't concede immediately)

**"How much does it cost?"**
→ Never give pricing in email. "Depends on what makes sense for where [Company] is right now — easier to figure out on a quick call. Are you open to 20 minutes?"

**No reply after full sequence**
→ Move to a different list. Don't follow up more than the sequence allows.

