## 12. DAILY EXECUTION RHYTHM

### Session Structure (2-hour sprint)
```
FIRST HOUR — Recording & Sending (non-negotiable)
├── 0:00–0:05  Pull today's target list (max 10–15 leads)
├── 0:05–0:35  Record Loom videos (4 min per video, 7–8 videos)
├── 0:35–0:50  Upload to Loom, set titles and CTA buttons
└── 0:50–1:00  Send cold emails + LinkedIn connection requests

SECOND HOUR — List Building & Research
├── 1:00–1:30  Screen new leads from Apollo (screenshot → qualify → credit)
├── 1:30–1:45  Research confirmed leads for next session
└── 1:45–2:00  Log all sends in tracker, note any replies
```

### Daily Target
- Minimum: 7 videos recorded and sent
- Goal: 10 videos recorded and sent
- Stretch: 15 videos recorded and sent

### Pre-Session Checklist
- [ ] Today's target list ready (10–15 qualified leads)
- [ ] Each company's website bookmarked and loadable
- [ ] Loom open and recording test done
- [ ] Scripts written or queued for each lead
- [ ] Calendly link live and working
- [ ] tj@signalux.co sending working
- [ ] LinkedIn open on desktop

