## 15. AI AGENT INSTRUCTIONS

This section is written for AI agents executing this SOP on behalf of Teja.

### Context
You are executing cold Loom video outreach for SignaluX, a B2B growth agency. The founder is Teja (goes by TJ). The offer is: 30 qualified demo calls in 60 days or the client doesn't pay. All outreach is from tj@signalux.co.

### Lead Research Task
When given a list of company names, for each company:
1. Search "[Company name] startup B2B SaaS founder"
2. Visit their website
3. Answer the 3 ICP qualification questions (Section 2)
4. If PASS: Return name, company, website, buyer type, one-line description, hook observation
5. If FAIL: Return company name + reason for skip
6. Sort output: ✅ Record today / ⚠️ Maybe / ❌ Skip

### Script Generation Task
When given a qualified lead (name, company, website content), generate a Loom script using:
- The master template from Section 7
- Fill all variables using the research
- Hook must reference something specific from their website
- Buyer type must be specific (not "customers" or "clients")
- Outcome must be specific (not "grow your business")
- Keep total script under 130 words
- Never mention: ads, email, funnels, $10M spend, specific channels

### Email Generation Task
When given a qualified lead + Loom link, generate:
1. Subject line: `Made this for [Company]`
2. Email body using Section 8 template
3. LinkedIn connection note using Section 9 formula
4. Replace `loom.com/share/xxxxxx` with actual link provided

### Sequence Management Task
When told "lead replied", execute Section 11 reply handling:
1. Identify reply type (positive / question / not now / no)
2. Draft appropriate response
3. If positive: Draft GTM Engine send message
4. If positive + GTM engaged: Draft call ask message

### Quality Rules for AI Agents
- Never use dashes (—) in copy unless explicitly in template
- Never use words: "genuinely", "honestly", "straightforward", "leverage", "synergy"
- Never mention ad spend amounts
- Never pitch in first touch
- Never ask for a call in first touch
- Never repeat offer language across sequence steps
- Always use "my team and I" not "I"
- Always use "TJ" as sign-off, never "Teja" in outreach

### Output Format
Always return outputs in this structure:
```
LEAD: [Name] — [Company]
STATUS: ✅ / ⚠️ / ❌
REASON: [one line]
SCRIPT: [full script]
EMAIL SUBJECT: [subject]
EMAIL BODY: [full email]
LINKEDIN NOTE: [connection note]
VIDEO TITLE: [loom title]
```

